=\"allsetlearning-di4.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone4\">dì</a> ]: the Four Noble Truths (Budd.), covered by the acronym <a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details/?word=%E8%8B%A6%E9%9B%86%E6%BB%85%E9%81%93\">苦集滅道</a> : all life is suffering <a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details/?word=%E8%8B%A6\">苦</a> , the cause of suffering is desire <a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details/?word=%E9%9B%86\">集</a> , emancipation comes only by eliminating passions <a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details/?word=%E7%81%AD\">灭</a> , the way <a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details/?word=%E9%81%93\">道</a> to emancipation is the Eight-fold Noble Way <a href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/dictionary-details/?word=%E5%85%AB%E6%AD%A3%E9%81%93\">八正道</a></span>\n<hr>\n<div>\n  <div>\n    <div><span class=\"tc\">(Trad.: 諦)</span></div>\n    <div><b>Pictophonetic</b>: <span class=\"semantic\"><a class=\"dictips\">帝</a></span> indicates the sound; <span class=\"phonetic\"><a class=\"dictips\">讠</a></span> (speech) conveys the meaning.</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div>Freq: 3338</div>\n<hr>\n<div><span style=\"color:#f5950f\">Hanzi:</span> 諦<br></div>\n<div>\n  <hr>\n</div>\n<div id=\"hanziyuan\">\n  <div class=\"etymology-nav\" id=\"&#x8C1B;\">\n    <div class=\"alert alert-success etymology-alert m-0\" role=\"alert\"></div>\n    <div class=\"row bg-info border-purple border-top mx-0 row-eq-height\" id=\"E01197\">\n      <div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-4 p-0\">\n        <div class=\"p-1\">\n          <p></p>\n          <p><b>Traditional in your browser 繁体字的浏览器显示:</b><span class=\"text-lg\">&#x8AE6;</span></p>\n          <p><b>Traditional in Unicode standard 繁体字的Unicode标准:</b><a href=\"https://www.unicode.org/cgi-bin/GetUnihanData.pl?codepoint=8AE6\" target=\"_blank\">U+8AE6</a><img src=\"https://www.unicode.org/cgi-bin/refglyph?24-8AE6\"></p>\n          <p><b>Older traditional characters 旧繁体字/异体字:</b> Not exist</p>\n          <p><b>Simplified in your browser 简体字的浏览器显示:</b><span class=\"text-lg\">&#x8C1B;</span></p>\n          <p><b>Simplified in Unicode standard 简体字的Unicode标准:</b><a href=\"https://www.unicode.org/cgi-bin/GetUnihanData.pl?codepoint=8C1B\" target=\"_blank\">U+8C1B</a><img src=\"https://www.unicode.org/cgi-bin/refglyph?24-8C1B\"></p>\n          <p><b>Main pronunciation 主要发音:</b> d&#xEC;</p>\n          <p><b>Other pronunciations 其它发音:</b> Not exists.</p>\n          <p><b>Original meaning 本义:</b> Meaning attentive.</p>\n          <p><b>English senses 英语理解:</b></p>\n          <p><b>Usage example 用法举例:</b> &#x771F;&#x8AE6; zh&#x113;n d&#xEC; (essence)</p>\n          <p><b>Importance by frequency 常用频率:</b></p>\n          <p><b>Shuowen 说文解字:</b> &#x5BE9;&#x4E5F;&#x543E;&#x5E1D;&#x8072;</p>\n          <p class=\"pre-inline\"><b>Character decomposition 字形分解 <a href=\"https://dixin.github.io/Etymology/decomposition-of-chinese-character\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Help: Decomposition of Chinese character\"></a>:</b><br>Compound &#x8AE6; &#xD;&#xA;from mouth-speak (&#x8BA0;)&#x8A01; y&#xE1;n and &#xD;&#xA;phonetic sheaf-king &#x5E1D; d&#xEC;&#xD;&#xA;simp &#x8C1B;.</p>\n          <p class=\"pre-inline\"><b>Decomposition notes 字形分解说明 <a href=\"https://dixin.github.io/Etymology/decomposition-of-chinese-character\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Help: Decomposition of Chinese character\"></a>:</b><br></p>\n          <p><b>Simplification rule <a target=\"_blank\"></a>:</b></p>\n          <p class=\"pre-inline\"><b>Simplification rule explained <a target=\"_blank\"></a>:</b><br></p>\n          <p><b>Variant rule :</b></p>\n          <p class=\"pre-inline\"><b>Variant rule clarification <a target=\"_blank\"></a>:</b><br></p>\n          <p><b>Applied rules <a target=\"_blank\"></a>:</b> R01 &#x8BA0;&#x8A01;&#x8A00;</p>\n          <p><b>New font rule <a target=\"_blank\"></a>:</b></p><a target=\"_blank\"><span></span></a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"p-1 bg-primary col-md-9 col-sm-8 etymology-result\" id=\"etymologyCharacters\">\n        <h3><span></span></h3>\n        <p>There is no known oracle characters found. 没.</p>\n        <hr>\n        <h3><span></span></h3>\n        <p>There is no known bronze characters found. 没.</p>\n        <hr>\n        <h3><span></span> Seal characters (1)</h3>\n        <ul class=\"list-inline list-unstyled\">\n          <li class=\"text-center\"><img src=\"hanziyan-S01694.png\"></li>\n        </ul>\n        <hr>\n        <h3><span></span> Liushutong characters (2)</h3>\n        <ul class=\"list-inline list-unstyled\">\n          <li class=\"text-center\"><img src=\"hanziyan-L19964.png\"></li>\n          <li class=\"text-center\"><img src=\"hanziyan-L19965.png\"></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"two_children__horiz_even\">\n  <div id=\"yw11\">\n    <h4><span>谛</span>字的基本解释</h4>\n    <div>\n      <p>谛<br>（諦）<br>dì<br>仔细：谛听。谛视。谛观。谛思。<br>道理：真谛。妙谛。<br><br></p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谛</span>字的汉语字典释义</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>[①]［dì］<br>［《廣韻》都計切，去霽，端。］<br>“谛1”的繁体字。<br>(1)注意；细察。<br>(2)仔细。参见“諦視”、“諦聽”。<br>(3)确凿；确实。<br>(4)领悟。<br>(5)佛教语。梵文Satya的意译。谓真实无谬的道理。<br>(6)泛指道理。<br>(7)同“帝”。<br>[②]［tí］<br>［《集韻》田黎切，平齊，定。］<br>通“啼1”。“谛2”的繁体字。<br>号哭。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谛</span>字的英文翻译</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>◎ <b>谛</b><br>attentively, carefully, meaning, significance</p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谛</span>字的康熙字典解释</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>【酉集上】【言字部】　諦； 康熙笔画：16； 页码：<a href=\"https://images.yw11.com/kangxi/1188.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><span>页1188第18</span></a><br>【唐韻】都計切【集韻】【韻會】【正韻】丁計切，?音帝。【說文】審也。【書·洪範·孔傳】必微諦。【疏】聽當別彼是非，必微妙而審諦也。【後漢·祭祀志】褅之爲言諦也。諦諟昭穆尊?之義。又【李雲傳】帝者，諦也。【註】審諦於物也。【魏志·明帝紀】君諦視之勿誤也。【關尹子·九藥篇】諦毫末者，不見天地之大。【劉勰·新論·專學篇】心不在學而强諷誦，雖入於耳而不諦於心。　又四諦。【魏書·釋老志】初根，人爲小乗，行四諦法。【釋典·心經】四諦：苦集滅道。苦謂生老病死，集謂集聚骨肉財帛，滅謂壞滅，道謂修行。又二諦：世諦以世俗顯緣起之事，諸法歷然，勸臣子以忠孝，勸家國以和治，此依俗諦。眞諦彰本寂之理，一性泯然，是非雙泯，能所俱亡，此依眞諦。　又【集韻】或作諟、?，互詳二字註。　又【集韻】田黎切，音題。號也。與嗁、謕?同。　又通作啼。【荀子·禮論篇】哭泣諦號。【註】啼、諦通用。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谛</span>字的源字形</div>\n    <div>\n      <p></p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谛</span>字的起名意思</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>意为道理，真理，详细，仔细等。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"yw11_en_transl\">meaning<br>Basic explanation of words<br>meaning<br>(meaning)<br>dì<br>Carefully: listen carefully. Dishi. Truth. Di Si.<br>Reason: the truth. Wonderful truth.<br>meaning<br>Chinese dictionary definition of words<br>[①]［dì］<br>[\"Guangyun\" all plan to cut, go to Ji, end. ]<br>\"谛1\" in traditional characters.<br>(1) Attention; careful inspection.<br>(2) Careful. See \"Division\", \"Division\".<br>(3) Conclusive; indeed.<br>(4) Comprehend.<br>(5) Buddhist language. Free translation of Satya in Sanskrit. The truth is true and infallible.<br>(6) Refers to truth in general.<br>(7) Same as \"di\".<br>[②]［tí］<br>[\"Jiyun\" Tian Liqie, level, set. ]<br>Same as \"Cry 1\". \"谛2\" in traditional characters.<br>Crying.<br>meaning<br>English translation of words<br>◎ Truth<br>attentively, carefully, meaning, significance<br>meaning<br>Kangxi dictionary interpretation of words<br>[You Ji 1] [Words Department] 　谛; Kangxi strokes: 16; Page number: page 1188 18<br>[Tang Yun] All Jiqie【Jiyun】【Yunhui】【Zhengyun】Ding Jiqie,? Yindi. [Said the text] Review also. 【Book·Hongfan·Kong Biography】It must be a little bit of truth. [Sparse] When listening to the right and wrong, you must be subtle and judge the truth. [Later Han · Sacrifice History] It is the truth of words. The righteousness of Di Yin Zhao Mu Zun? Also 【Li Yun Chuan】The emperor, the truth is also. [Note] Examining the essence of things is also true. [Wei Zhi·Ming Di Ji] You should never miss it. 【Guan Yinzi·Nine Medicines】The one who has the lowest truth can't see the greatness of the world. 【Liu Xie·New Theory·Specialized Study】The heart is not learning but strong satire, although it is in the ear but not in the heart.　Four truths. [Wei Shu·Lao Zhi] The first root, the human is the Hinayana, practicing the Four Noble Truths. 【Explanation Code·Heart Sutra】Four Noble Truths: Suffering Settlement. Suffering means birth, old age, sickness and death, collection means gathering of flesh and blood, destruction means destruction, and Tao means cultivation. Another two truths: The world truth is based on the secular world to show the origin of things. The laws are all in order to persuade the courtiers to be loyal and filial, and to persuade the family and the country to govern by harmony. This follows the customary truth. Sui Di expresses the truth of the original solitude, one nature is obscure, right and wrong are dual, and everything can perish, and this depends on Sui Di.　 [Ji Yun] or make 諟, ?, the two-character note for mutual details.　[Jiyun] Tian Liqie, phonetic title. No. also. Same as huh and hu?　Through again. 【Xunzi·Ritual Theory】The cry of the truth. [Note] Cry and truth are common.<br>meaning<br>Source glyph<br>meaning<br>Name meaning<br>It means truth, truth, detail, carefulness, etc.</div>\n</div>\n<div><a href=\"https://images.yw11.com/zixing/zi148274000653393.png\" target=\"_blank\"><object data=\"https://images.yw11.com/zixing/zi148274000653393.png\" type=\"image/png\"><img src=\"yw11-zixing-zi148274000653393.png\"></object></a></div>\n<div class=\"two_children__horiz_even\">\n  <div id=\"yw11_image_chinese\">トrodrr<br>谛<br>形声字。言(i)表意,其形像张口说话状;帝(d)表声,帝指君主、天神,表示仔细领会听取君主、天神的言语、指示。<br>声旁简化。本义是仔细。<br>①仔细:~听|~视。②意义;道理:真~「妙~。<br>dì<br>~观 ~视 ~听 妙~ 真~<br>諦諦<br>諦|谛<br>篆<br>楷</div>\n  <div id=\"yw11_image_ru_transl\">имея в виду<br>Пиктофонетические символы.<br>Ян (i) выражает смысл, и его изображение похоже на открытый рот; император (d) выражает голос, император относится к монарху и богу, что означает, что он внимательно понимает и слушает слова и инструкции монарха и бога.<br>Голосовое упрощение.<br>Первоначальный смысл осторожен.<br>① Осторожно: ~ Слушай | ~ Смотри.<br>② Значение; причина: правда ~ \"Чудо ~.<br>~ Просмотр ~ Смотрите ~ Слушайте ~ Действительно ~<br>Правда<br>Правда | Правда<br>тюлень<br>Кай</div>\n</div>\n<hr>\n<div id=\"bkrs_pinyin\">dì, tí</div>\n<div id=\"bkrs_transl\">\n  <div><strong>I</strong><i> гл.</i></div>\n  <div>1) <strong>dì</strong> рассматривать, всматриваться в; исследовать, вникать; всматриваясь, внимательно</div>\n  <div><span class=\"example-item\">谛思 тщательно продумывать</span></div>\n  <div><span class=\"example-item\">谛毫末者, 不见天地之大 всматривающийся в кончик волоска не увидит величия неба и земли</span></div>\n  <div>2) <strong>dì</strong> запечатлеться, усвоиться</div>\n  <div><span class=\"example-item\">不谛于心 не запечатлеться в душе</span></div>\n  <div>3) <strong>tí</strong> *<i> вм.</i> 啼 (<i>кричать; плакать</i>)</div>\n  <div><strong>II dì</strong><i> сущ.</i></div>\n  <div><span class=\"paragraph\">будд.</span> истина; постижение истины; духовное просветление</div>\n  <div><span class=\"example-item\">真谛 абсолютная истина (paramārtha-satya)</span></div>\n</div>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mdbg.net/chinese/dictionary?page=worddict&wdrst=0&wdqtm=0&wdqcham=1&wdqt=\">MDBG</a> | <a href=\"https://bkrs.info/slovo.php?ch=谛\">BKRS</a> | <a href=\"https://dictionary.writtenchinese.com/#sk=谛&svt=pinyin\">WriCh</a> | <a href=\"http://www.qianyix.com/words/index.php?q=谛\">Qianyix</a> | <a href=\"https://www.yellowbridge.com/chinese/sentsearch.php?word=谛\">YBridge</a> | <a href=\"http://cca.xingtanlu.cn/?action=page&pid=8&do=search&name=谛\">Collocs</a> | <a href=\"https://characterpop.com/explode/谛\">ChPop</a> | <a href=\"https://visualchinesesearch.com/?query=谛\">SimCh</a> | <a href=\"http://www.hanzicraft.com/character/谛\">Stats</a> | <a href=\"https://www.google.com.au/search?q=谛&tbm=isch\">Google Images</a> | <a href=\"https://namakajiri.net/kanjigen/#谛\">Char lookup site</a></p>","glyphs":[{"glyph":"讠","pinyins":["yan2"]},{"glyph":"帝","pinyins":["di4"]}],"isMentionedAt__hanziyuan_without_charactersWithComponent":["諦"]}